264// Lookup Binary Search Utility BINARYSEARCH_U16_Near_iL



265void BINARYSEARCH_U16_Near_iL(uint32_T *piLeft, uint16_T u, const uint16_T



266  *pData, uint32_T iHi)



267{



268  uint32_T iRght;



269



270  // Find the location of current input value in the data table.



271  *piLeft = 0U;



272  iRght = iHi;



273  if (u <= pData[0] ) {



274    // Less than or equal to the smallest point in the table.



275  } else if (u >= pData[iHi] ) {



276    // Greater than or equal to the largest point in the table.



277    *piLeft = iHi;



278  } else {



279    uint32_T i;



280



281    // Do a binary search.



282    while (( iRght - *piLeft ) > 1U ) {



283      // Get the average of the left and right indices using to Floor rounding.



284      i = (*piLeft + iRght) >> 1;



285



286      // Move either the right index or the left index so that



287      //  LeftDataPoint <= CurrentValue < RightDataPoint



288      if (u < pData[i] ) {



289        iRght = i;



290      } else {



291        *piLeft = i;



292      }



293    }



294



295    // Adjust the left index, if necessary, so that it always gives



296    // the index of the data point nearest the current input value.



297    {



298      uint32_T diffLeft, diffRght;



299      diffLeft = u - pData[*piLeft];



300      diffRght = pData[iRght] - u;



301      if (diffRght <= diffLeft ) {



302        *piLeft = iRght;



303      }



304    }



305  }



306}

308// Lookup Binary Search Utility BINARYSEARCH_U16



309void BINARYSEARCH_U16(uint32_T *piLeft, uint32_T *piRght, uint16_T u, const



310                      uint16_T *pData, uint32_T iHi)



311{



312  // Find the location of current input value in the data table.



313  *piLeft = 0U;



314  *piRght = iHi;



315  if (u <= pData[0] ) {



316    // Less than or equal to the smallest point in the table.



317    *piRght = 0U;



318  } else if (u >= pData[iHi] ) {



319    // Greater than or equal to the largest point in the table.



320    *piLeft = iHi;



321  } else {



322    uint32_T i;



323



324    // Do a binary search.



325    while (( *piRght - *piLeft ) > 1U ) {



326      // Get the average of the left and right indices using to Floor rounding.



327      i = (*piLeft + *piRght) >> 1;



328



329      // Move either the right index or the left index so that



330      //  LeftDataPoint <= CurrentValue < RightDataPoint



331      if (u < pData[i] ) {



332        *piRght = i;



333      } else {



334        *piLeft = i;



335      }



336    }



337  }



338}

340// Lookup Interpolation INTERPOLATE_U16_U16



341void INTERPOLATE_U16_U16(uint16_T *pY, uint16_T yL, uint16_T yR, uint16_T x,



342  uint16_T xL, uint16_T xR)



343{



344  uint32_T bigProd;



345  uint16_T yDiff;



346  uint16_T xNum;



347  uint16_T xDen;



348  *pY = yL;



349



350  // If x is not strictly between xR and xL



351  //  then an interpolation calculation is not necessary x == xL



352  //  or not valid.  The invalid situation is expected when the input



353  //  is beyond the left or right end of the table.  The design is



354  //  that yL holds the correct value for *pY



355  //  in invalid situations.



356



357  if ((xR > xL) && (x > xL) ) {



358    xDen = xR;



359    xDen = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)xDen - (uint32_T)xL);



360    xNum = x;



361    xNum = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)xNum - (uint32_T)xL);



362    if (yR >= yL ) {



363      yDiff = yR;



364      yDiff = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff - (uint32_T)yL);



365    } else {



366      yDiff = yL;



367      yDiff = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff - (uint32_T)yR);



368    }



369



370    bigProd = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff * (uint32_T)xNum);



371



372    {



373      uint32_T rtb_u32_tmp;



374      rtb_u32_tmp = (uint32_T)xDen;



375      yDiff = (uint16_T)(rtb_u32_tmp == 0U ? MAX_uint32_T : (uint32_T)(bigProd /



376        rtb_u32_tmp));



377    }



378



379    if (yR >= yL ) {



380      *pY = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY + (uint32_T)yDiff);



381    } else {



382      *pY = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY - (uint32_T)yDiff);



383    }



384  }



385}

387// Lookup Utility LookUp_U16_U16



388void LookUp_U16_U16(uint16_T *pY, const uint16_T *pYData, uint16_T u, const



389                    uint16_T *pUData, uint32_T iHi)



390{



391  uint32_T iLeft;



392  uint32_T iRght;



393  BINARYSEARCH_U16( &(iLeft), &(iRght), u, pUData, iHi);



394  INTERPOLATE_U16_U16( pY, pYData[iLeft], pYData[iRght], u, pUData[iLeft],



395                      pUData[iRght]);



396}

398// Lookup Evenly Spaced Interpolation INTERPOLATE_EVEN_U16_U16_SAT



399void INTERPOLATE_EVEN_U16_U16_SAT(uint16_T *pY, uint16_T yL, uint16_T yR,



400  uint16_T xMinusxL, uint16_T xSpacing)



401{



402  uint32_T bigProd;



403  uint16_T yDiff;



404  *pY = yL;



405  if (yR >= yL ) {



406    yDiff = yR;



407



408    {



409      uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



410      uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



411      rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)yDiff;



412      rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yL);



413      if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



414        rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



415      }



416



417      if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



418        rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



419      }



420



421      yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



422    }



423  } else {



424    yDiff = yL;



425



426    {



427      uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



428      uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



429      rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)yDiff;



430      rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yR);



431      if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



432        rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



433      }



434



435      if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



436        rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



437      }



438



439      yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



440    }



441  }



442



443  bigProd = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff * (uint32_T)xMinusxL);



444



445  {



446    uint32_T rtb_u32_tmp;



447    rtb_u32_tmp = (uint32_T)xSpacing;



448    rtb_u32_tmp = rtb_u32_tmp == 0U ? MAX_uint32_T : (uint32_T)(bigProd /



449      rtb_u32_tmp);



450    if (rtb_u32_tmp > 65535U) {



451      rtb_u32_tmp = 65535U;



452    }



453



454    yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_tmp;



455  }



456



457  if (yR >= yL ) {



458    {



459      uint32_T rtb_u32_tmp;



460      rtb_u32_tmp = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY + (uint32_T)yDiff);



461      if (rtb_u32_tmp > 65535U) {



462        rtb_u32_tmp = 65535U;



463      }



464



465      *pY = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_tmp;



466    }



467  } else {



468    {



469      uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



470      uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



471      rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)*pY;



472      rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yDiff);



473      if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



474        rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



475      }



476



477      if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



478        rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



479      }



480



481      *pY = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



482    }



483  }



484}

486// Lookup 1D UtilityLookUpEven_U16_U16_SAT



487void LookUpEven_U16_U16_SAT(uint16_T *pY, const uint16_T *pYData, uint16_T u,



488  uint16_T valueLo, uint32_T iHi, uint16_T uSpacing)



489{



490  if (u <= valueLo ) {



491    (*pY) = (*pYData);



492  } else {



493    uint32_T uAdjusted = u - valueLo;



494    uint32_T iLeft = uAdjusted / uSpacing;



495    if (iLeft >= iHi ) {



496      (*pY) = pYData[iHi];



497    } else {



498      INTERPOLATE_EVEN_U16_U16_SAT( pY, pYData[iLeft], pYData[((iLeft)+1)],



499        ((uint16_T)((uAdjusted-(iLeft*uSpacing)))), uSpacing);



500    }



501  }



502}

504// Lookup Interpolation INTERPOLATE_U16_U16_SAT



505void INTERPOLATE_U16_U16_SAT(uint16_T *pY, uint16_T yL, uint16_T yR, uint16_T x,



506  uint16_T xL, uint16_T xR)



507{



508  uint32_T bigProd;



509  uint16_T yDiff;



510  uint16_T xNum;



511  uint16_T xDen;



512  *pY = yL;



513



514  // If x is not strictly between xR and xL



515  //  then an interpolation calculation is not necessary x == xL



516  //  or not valid.  The invalid situation is expected when the input



517  //  is beyond the left or right end of the table.  The design is



518  //  that yL holds the correct value for *pY



519  //  in invalid situations.



520



521  if ((xR > xL) && (x > xL) ) {



522    xDen = xR;



523



524    {



525      uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



526      uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



527      rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)xDen;



528      rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)xL);



529      if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



530        rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



531      }



532



533      if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



534        rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



535      }



536



537      xDen = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



538    }



539



540    xNum = x;



541



542    {



543      uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



544      uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



545      rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)xNum;



546      rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)xL);



547      if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



548        rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



549      }



550



551      if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



552        rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



553      }



554



555      xNum = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



556    }



557



558    if (yR >= yL ) {



559      yDiff = yR;



560



561      {



562        uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



563        uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



564        rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)yDiff;



565        rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yL);



566        if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



567          rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



568        }



569



570        if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



571          rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



572        }



573



574        yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



575      }



576    } else {



577      yDiff = yL;



578



579      {



580        uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



581        uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



582        rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)yDiff;



583        rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yR);



584        if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



585          rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



586        }



587



588        if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



589          rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



590        }



591



592        yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



593      }



594    }



595



596    bigProd = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff * (uint32_T)xNum);



597



598    {



599      uint32_T rtb_u32_tmp;



600      rtb_u32_tmp = (uint32_T)xDen;



601      rtb_u32_tmp = rtb_u32_tmp == 0U ? MAX_uint32_T : (uint32_T)(bigProd /



602        rtb_u32_tmp);



603      if (rtb_u32_tmp > 65535U) {



604        rtb_u32_tmp = 65535U;



605      }



606



607      yDiff = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_tmp;



608    }



609



610    if (yR >= yL ) {



611      {



612        uint32_T rtb_u32_tmp;



613        rtb_u32_tmp = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY + (uint32_T)yDiff);



614        if (rtb_u32_tmp > 65535U) {



615          rtb_u32_tmp = 65535U;



616        }



617



618        *pY = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_tmp;



619      }



620    } else {



621      {



622        uint32_T rtb_u32_q0;



623        uint32_T rtb_u32_qY;



624        rtb_u32_q0 = (uint32_T)*pY;



625        rtb_u32_qY = (uint32_T)(rtb_u32_q0 - (uint32_T)yDiff);



626        if (rtb_u32_qY > rtb_u32_q0) {



627          rtb_u32_qY = 0U;



628        }



629



630        if (rtb_u32_qY > 65535U) {



631          rtb_u32_qY = 65535U;



632        }



633



634        *pY = (uint16_T)rtb_u32_qY;



635      }



636    }



637  }



638}

641void LookUp_U16_U16_SAT(uint16_T *pY, const uint16_T *pYData, uint16_T u, const



642  uint16_T *pUData, uint32_T iHi)



643{



644  uint32_T iLeft;



645  uint32_T iRght;



646  BINARYSEARCH_U16( &(iLeft), &(iRght), u, pUData, iHi);



647  INTERPOLATE_U16_U16_SAT( pY, pYData[iLeft], pYData[iRght], u, pUData[iLeft],



648    pUData[iRght]);

651// Lookup Binary Search Utility BINARYSEARCH_U16_iL



652void BINARYSEARCH_U16_iL(uint32_T *piLeft, uint16_T u, const uint16_T *pData,



653  uint32_T iHi)



654{



655  uint32_T iRght;



656



657  // Find the location of current input value in the data table.



658  *piLeft = 0U;



659  iRght = iHi;



660  if (u <= pData[0] ) {



661    // Less than or equal to the smallest point in the table.



662  } else if (u >= pData[iHi] ) {



663    // Greater than or equal to the largest point in the table.



664    *piLeft = iHi;



665  } else {



666    uint32_T i;



667



668    // Do a binary search.



669    while (( iRght - *piLeft ) > 1U ) {



670      // Get the average of the left and right indices using to Floor rounding.



671      i = (*piLeft + iRght) >> 1;



672



673      // Move either the right index or the left index so that



674      //  LeftDataPoint <= CurrentValue < RightDataPoint



675      if (u < pData[i] ) {



676        iRght = i;



677      } else {



678        *piLeft = i;



679      }



680    }



681  }



682}



683



684// Lookup Binary Search Utility BINARYSEARCH_S16



685void BINARYSEARCH_S16(uint32_T *piLeft, uint32_T *piRght, int16_T u, const



686                      int16_T *pData, uint32_T iHi)



687{



688  // Find the location of current input value in the data table.



689  *piLeft = 0U;



690  *piRght = iHi;



691  if (u <= pData[0] ) {



692    // Less than or equal to the smallest point in the table.



693    *piRght = 0U;



694  } else if (u >= pData[iHi] ) {



695    // Greater than or equal to the largest point in the table.



696    *piLeft = iHi;



697  } else {



698    uint32_T i;



699



700    // Do a binary search.



701    while (( *piRght - *piLeft ) > 1U ) {



702      // Get the average of the left and right indices using to Floor rounding.



703      i = (*piLeft + *piRght) >> 1;



704



705      // Move either the right index or the left index so that



706      //  LeftDataPoint <= CurrentValue < RightDataPoint



707      if (u < pData[i] ) {



708        *piRght = i;



709      } else {



710        *piLeft = i;



711      }



712    }



713  }



714}

716// Lookup Interpolation INTERPOLATE_U16_S16



717void INTERPOLATE_U16_S16(uint16_T *pY, uint16_T yL, uint16_T yR, int16_T x,



718  int16_T xL, int16_T xR)



719{



720  int32_T bigProd;



721  uint16_T yDiff;



722  int16_T xNum;



723  int16_T xDen;



724  *pY = yL;



725



726  // If x is not strictly between xR and xL



727  //  then an interpolation calculation is not necessary x == xL



728  //  or not valid.  The invalid situation is expected when the input



729  //  is beyond the left or right end of the table.  The design is



730  //  that yL holds the correct value for *pY



731  //  in invalid situations.



732



733  if ((xR > xL) && (x > xL) ) {



734    xDen = xR;



735    xDen = (int16_T)(int32_T)((int32_T)xDen - (int32_T)xL);



736    xNum = x;



737    xNum = (int16_T)(int32_T)((int32_T)xNum - (int32_T)xL);



738    if (yR >= yL ) {



739      yDiff = yR;



740      yDiff = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff - (uint32_T)yL);



741    } else {



742      yDiff = yL;



743      yDiff = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)yDiff - (uint32_T)yR);



744    }



745



746    bigProd = (int32_T)((int32_T)yDiff * (int32_T)xNum);



747    yDiff = (uint16_T)div_s32_floor(bigProd, (int32_T)xDen);



748    if (yR >= yL ) {



749      *pY = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY + (uint32_T)yDiff);



750    } else {



751      *pY = (uint16_T)(uint32_T)((uint32_T)*pY - (uint32_T)yDiff);



752    }



753  }



754}

756// Lookup Utility LookUp_U16_S16



757void LookUp_U16_S16(uint16_T *pY, const uint16_T *pYData, int16_T u, const



758                    int16_T *pUData, uint32_T iHi)



759{



760  uint32_T iLeft;



761  uint32_T iRght;



762  BINARYSEARCH_S16( &(iLeft), &(iRght), u, pUData, iHi);



763  INTERPOLATE_U16_S16( pY, pYData[iLeft], pYData[iRght], u, pUData[iLeft],



764                      pUData[iRght]);



765}

767int32_T div_s32(int32_T numerator, int32_T denominator)



768{



769  int32_T quotient;



770  uint32_T tempAbsQuotient;



771  if (denominator == 0) {



772    quotient = numerator >= 0 ? MAX_int32_T : MIN_int32_T;



773



774    // Divide by zero handler



775  } else {



776    tempAbsQuotient = (uint32_T)((numerator < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)



777      ~(uint32_T)numerator + 1U) : (uint32_T)numerator) / (denominator < 0 ?



778      (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)denominator + 1U) : (uint32_T)denominator));



779    quotient = (numerator < 0) != (denominator < 0) ? (int32_T)-(int32_T)



780      tempAbsQuotient : (int32_T)tempAbsQuotient;



781  }



782



783  return quotient;



784}

786int16_T div_s16u32(uint32_T numerator, uint32_T denominator)



787{



788  int16_T quotient;



789  if (denominator == 0U) {



790    quotient = MAX_int16_T;



791



792    // Divide by zero handler



793  } else {



794    quotient = (int16_T)(uint32_T)(numerator / denominator);



795  }



796



797  return quotient;



798}

800void mul_wide_su32(int32_T in0, uint32_T in1, uint32_T *ptrOutBitsHi, uint32_T



801                   *ptrOutBitsLo)



802{



803  uint32_T outBitsLo;



804  uint32_T absIn0;



805  uint32_T in0Hi;



806  uint32_T in1Lo;



807  uint32_T in1Hi;



808  uint32_T productHiLo;



809  uint32_T productLoHi;



810  absIn0 = in0 < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)in0 + 1U) : (uint32_T)in0;



811  in0Hi = (uint32_T)(absIn0 >> 16U);



812  absIn0 &= 65535U;



813  in1Hi = (uint32_T)(in1 >> 16U);



814  in1Lo = (uint32_T)(in1 & 65535U);



815  productHiLo = (uint32_T)(in0Hi * in1Lo);



816  productLoHi = (uint32_T)(absIn0 * in1Hi);



817  absIn0 *= in1Lo;



818  in1Lo = 0U;



819  outBitsLo = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)(productLoHi << 16U) + absIn0);



820  if (outBitsLo < absIn0) {



821    in1Lo = 1U;



822  }



823



824  absIn0 = outBitsLo;



825  outBitsLo += (uint32_T)(productHiLo << 16U);



826  if (outBitsLo < absIn0) {



827    in1Lo++;



828  }



829



830  absIn0 = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)((uint32_T)((uint32_T)(productLoHi >> 16U) +



831    (uint32_T)(productHiLo >> 16U)) + (uint32_T)(in0Hi * in1Hi)) + in1Lo);



832  if (!((in1 == 0U) || (in0 >= 0))) {



833    absIn0 = (uint32_T)~absIn0;



834    outBitsLo = (uint32_T)~outBitsLo;



835    outBitsLo++;



836    if (outBitsLo == 0U) {



837      absIn0++;



838    }



839  }



840



841  *ptrOutBitsHi = absIn0;



842  *ptrOutBitsLo = outBitsLo;



843}

845uint32_T mul_usu32_loSR(int32_T a, uint32_T b, uint32_T aShift)



846{



847  uint32_T result;



848  uint32_T u32_chi;



849  mul_wide_su32(a, b, &u32_chi, &result);



850  return (uint32_T)((uint32_T)(u32_chi << (uint32_T)(32U - aShift)) | (uint32_T)



851                    (result >> aShift));



852}

854int32_T div_repeat_s32_near(int32_T numerator, int32_T denominator, uint32_T



855  nRepeatSub)



856{



857  int32_T quotient;



858  uint32_T tempAbsQuotient;



859  boolean_T quotientNeedsNegation;



860  uint32_T absNumerator;



861  uint32_T absDenominator;



862  uint32_T iRepeatSub;



863  boolean_T numeratorExtraBit;



864  if (denominator == 0) {



865    quotient = numerator >= 0 ? MAX_int32_T : MIN_int32_T;



866



867    // Divide by zero handler



868  } else {



869    absNumerator = numerator < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)numerator +



870      1U) : (uint32_T)numerator;



871    absDenominator = denominator < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)



872      denominator + 1U) : (uint32_T)denominator;



873    quotientNeedsNegation = ((numerator < 0) != (denominator < 0));



874    tempAbsQuotient = (uint32_T)(absNumerator / absDenominator);



875    absNumerator %= absDenominator;



876    for (iRepeatSub = 0U; iRepeatSub < nRepeatSub; iRepeatSub++) {



877      numeratorExtraBit = (absNumerator >= 2147483648U);



878      absNumerator <<= 1U;



879      tempAbsQuotient <<= 1U;



880      if (numeratorExtraBit || (absNumerator >= absDenominator)) {



881        tempAbsQuotient++;



882        absNumerator -= absDenominator;



883      }



884    }



885



886    numeratorExtraBit = (absNumerator >= 2147483648U);



887    absNumerator <<= 1U;



888    if (numeratorExtraBit || (quotientNeedsNegation ? absNumerator >



889         absDenominator : absNumerator >= absDenominator)) {



890      tempAbsQuotient++;



891    }



892



893    quotient = quotientNeedsNegation ? (int32_T)-(int32_T)tempAbsQuotient :



894      (int32_T)tempAbsQuotient;



895  }



896



897  return quotient;



898}



899



900uint32_T div_u32_near(uint32_T numerator, uint32_T denominator)



901{



902  uint32_T quotient;



903  if (denominator == 0U) {



904    quotient = MAX_uint32_T;



905



906    // Divide by zero handler



907  } else {



908    quotient = (uint32_T)(numerator / denominator);



909    numerator %= denominator;



910    if ((numerator > 2147483647U) || ((uint32_T)(numerator << 1U) >= denominator))



911    {



912      quotient++;



913    }



914  }



915



916  return quotient;



917}

919void mul_wide_s32(int32_T in0, int32_T in1, uint32_T *ptrOutBitsHi, uint32_T



920                  *ptrOutBitsLo)



921{



922  uint32_T absIn0;



923  uint32_T absIn1;



924  uint32_T in0Lo;



925  uint32_T in0Hi;



926  uint32_T in1Hi;



927  uint32_T productHiLo;



928  uint32_T productLoHi;



929  absIn0 = in0 < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)in0 + 1U) : (uint32_T)in0;



930  absIn1 = in1 < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)in1 + 1U) : (uint32_T)in1;



931  in0Hi = (uint32_T)(absIn0 >> 16U);



932  in0Lo = (uint32_T)(absIn0 & 65535U);



933  in1Hi = (uint32_T)(absIn1 >> 16U);



934  absIn0 = (uint32_T)(absIn1 & 65535U);



935  productHiLo = (uint32_T)(in0Hi * absIn0);



936  productLoHi = (uint32_T)(in0Lo * in1Hi);



937  absIn0 *= in0Lo;



938  absIn1 = 0U;



939  in0Lo = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)(productLoHi << 16U) + absIn0);



940  if (in0Lo < absIn0) {



941    absIn1 = 1U;



942  }



943



944  absIn0 = in0Lo;



945  in0Lo += (uint32_T)(productHiLo << 16U);



946  if (in0Lo < absIn0) {



947    absIn1++;



948  }



949



950  absIn0 = (uint32_T)((uint32_T)((uint32_T)((uint32_T)(productLoHi >> 16U) +



951    (uint32_T)(productHiLo >> 16U)) + (uint32_T)(in0Hi * in1Hi)) + absIn1);



952  if (!((in0 == 0) || ((in1 == 0) || ((in0 > 0) == (in1 > 0))))) {



953    absIn0 = (uint32_T)~absIn0;



954    in0Lo = (uint32_T)~in0Lo;



955    in0Lo++;



956    if (in0Lo == 0U) {



957      absIn0++;



958    }



959  }



960



961  *ptrOutBitsHi = absIn0;



962  *ptrOutBitsLo = in0Lo;



963}

965int32_T mul_s32_hiSR(int32_T a, int32_T b, uint32_T aShift)



966{

968  uint32_T u32_clo;



969  mul_wide_s32(a, b, &u32_chi, &u32_clo);



970  return (int32_T)((int32_T)u32_chi >> aShift);

973int32_T div_s32_floor(int32_T numerator, int32_T denominator)



974{



975  int32_T quotient;



976  uint32_T absNumerator;



977  uint32_T absDenominator;



978  uint32_T tempAbsQuotient;



979  boolean_T quotientNeedsNegation;



980  if (denominator == 0) {



981    quotient = numerator >= 0 ? MAX_int32_T : MIN_int32_T;



982



983    // Divide by zero handler



984  } else {



985    absNumerator = numerator < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)numerator +



986      1U) : (uint32_T)numerator;



987    absDenominator = denominator < 0 ? (uint32_T)((uint32_T)~(uint32_T)



988      denominator + 1U) : (uint32_T)denominator;



989    quotientNeedsNegation = ((numerator < 0) != (denominator < 0));



990    tempAbsQuotient = (uint32_T)(absNumerator / absDenominator);



991    if (quotientNeedsNegation) {



992      absNumerator %= absDenominator;



993      if (absNumerator > 0U) {



994        tempAbsQuotient++;



995      }



996    }



997



998    quotient = quotientNeedsNegation ? (int32_T)-(int32_T)tempAbsQuotient :



999      (int32_T)tempAbsQuotient;



1000  }



1001



1002  return quotient;



1003}

1005//



1006//    This function updates active task flag for each subrate.



1007//  The function is called at model base rate, hence the



1008//  generated code self-manages all its subrates.



1009



1010static void rate_scheduler(void)



1011{



1012  // Compute which subrates run during the next base time step.  Subrates



1013  //  are an integer multiple of the base rate counter.  Therefore, the subtask



1014  //  counter is reset when it reaches its limit (zero means run).



1015



1016  (MX_Gateway_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2])++;



1017  if ((MX_Gateway_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2]) > 9) {// Sample time: [0.1s, 0.0s] 



1018    MX_Gateway_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2] = 0;



1019  }



1020}

4744  // The "clockTick0" counts the number of times the code of this task has



4745  //  been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick0"



4746  //  and "Timing.stepSize0". Size of "clockTick0" ensures timer will not



4747  //  overflow during the application lifespan selected.



4748  //  Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.



4749  //  The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick0 and the high bits



4750  //  Timing.clockTickH0. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.



4751



4752  if (!(++MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTick0)) {



4753    ++MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTickH0;



4754  }



4755



4756  MX_Gateway_M->Timing.t[0] = MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTick0 *



4757    MX_Gateway_M->Timing.stepSize0 + MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTickH0 *



4758    MX_Gateway_M->Timing.stepSize0 * 4294967296.0;



4759



4760  {

4762    // The "clockTick1" counts the number of times the code of this task has



4763    //  been executed. The resolution of this integer timer is 0.01, which is the step size



4764    //  of the task. Size of "clockTick1" ensures timer will not overflow during the



4765    //  application lifespan selected.



4766    //  Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.



4767    //  The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick1 and the high bits



4768    //  Timing.clockTickH1. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.



4769



4770    MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTick1++;



4771    if (!MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTick1) {



4772      MX_Gateway_M->Timing.clockTickH1++;



4773    }



4774  }



4775



4776  rate_scheduler();



4777}
